- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper is about developing a motion model for robots to perform human-like handovers. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper discusses the importance of soft factors such as predictability and safety in robot-human interaction. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possible category as the paper may involve computer vision techniques for observing and measuring joint movements in human-human handover. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper may involve AI techniques for developing the joint motion model. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper may involve machine learning techniques for developing the joint motion model.
